name: Black Hornbill
rangeDescription: Malay peninsula, sumatra, and borneo
description: Sooty black bird with a large, heavy bill that is bone-white in males, dark in females. Some males have a bright white eyebrow, while others have an entirely black head.

name: Yellow-green Brushfinch
rangeDescription: Humid montane forest of western panama
description: Hefty, long-tailed finch with a very limited range in western Panama. Its olive-greenish body with contrasting black head and bright yellow tufts at the base of each leg make this bird distinctive.

name: Red-collared Woodpecker
rangeDescription: Southwestern china (far southern yunnan) to laos and vietnam
description: Distinctive olive-green woodpecker with a shawl-like red pattern on the head. Male is essentially red-headed except for a pale throat and a green ear patch, while female lacks the red crown and has less red on the nape.

name: Red-throated Parrotfinch
rangeDescription: New caledonia
description: Tiny fluorescent green-and-red finch, found only on New Caledonia and the nearby Isle of Pines. Inhabits forest edge, as well as other open wooded habitats, such as scrubby plantation margins, grassy forest clearings, coastal scrub, and mangroves.

name: Black-capped Bulbul
rangeDescription: Sri lanka
description: Medium-sized greenish bird with a bright yellow underside and black head. Occurs in a variety of habitats, wherever there are trees, including forest, open woodlands, and gardens, in the lowlands and foothills.

name: Indian Courser
rangeDescription: Patchily distributed pakistan to india and sri lanka
description: Elegant and stately large plover-like bird. Note typically erect posture, strong black-and-white brow pattern, orange-suffused crown and chest, and slightly downcurved dark bill.

name: Olive Honeyeater
rangeDescription: Moluccas and raja ampat islands (off western new guinea)
description: A nondescript sparrow-sized songbird with a slender, downcurved bill. Entirely olive-green above and uniform pale gray below, but note head pattern, which includes a prominent whitish smudge on the cheeks and dull bare skin below the eye.

name: Collared Crow
rangeDescription: Central and eastern china to northern vietnam; hainan and taiwan
description: By far the most distinctive crow of farmland, fields, and other open spaces: adults black with white hindneck connecting to white breast band. Superficially similar to adult Daurian Jackdaw, but the latter is more compact and smaller, with pale plumage extending through the belly.

name: Tanzanian Red-billed Hornbill
rangeDescription: Central and southern tanzania
description: A fairly small, slim, long-tailed hornbill. Note the red bill, the dark eye with a ring of black skin, and the heavily spotted back.

name: Hooded Visorbearer
rangeDescription: Locally in northeastern brazilian plateaux (bahia and minas gerais)
description: Small, strikingly beautiful hummingbird with a short straight bill. Males have a distinctive head pattern: a black forehead and cheeks framing the green around the bill and a small golden patch on the throat.

name: White-rumped Snowfinch
rangeDescription: Tibet to western china (kokonor and nan shan mountains to sichuan)
description: A frosty little finch with a black patch around the eye and bright white wing patches and tail edges. Forages in high-altitude meadows, pastures, and grasslands, as well as in towns and monasteries, around which it can often be quite tame.

name: Long-crested Pygmy-Tyrant
rangeDescription: Far southwestern amazonian brazil, adjacent southeastern peru, and far northwestern bolivia
description: Small, tufted flycatcher found locally in lowland rainforest. Perches upright, making quick flights between perches to catch flying insects.

name: Black-headed Shrike-Babbler
rangeDescription: Nepal to bhutan, assam, northern myanmar, sichuan, northwestern yunnan, and northwestern vietnam (fansipan mountain)
description: Large-headed songbird with confusingly dissimilar male and female plumages. Male has an orange back, white throat, orangish belly, and a black head and wings.

name: Cassin's Finch
rangeDescription: Mountains of southwestern canada to central mexico and southern baja california
description: Males have red concentrated on crown (brighter than throat) with pinkish wash coming into breast; flanks are pale with only a few fine streaks. Females are similar to Purple Finch but with more diffuse face pattern and finer streaks on flanks.

name: Restinga Tyrannulet
rangeDescription: Coastal southeastern brazil (southeastern são paulo to northeastern santa catarina)
description: Small olive-green flycatcher with a long slender tail that is often held cocked. Note the yellow eyebrow, yellow throat, and two wingbars.

name: Inca Dove
rangeDescription: Semiarid southwestern usa to northwestern costa rica
description: Essentially a ground dove with a long tail. Pale sandy color with scaly pattern covering entire body, unlike Common Ground Dove.

name: Chestnut-crested Yuhina
rangeDescription: Montane forest of northern borneo
description: This sprightly and social little bird is the only yuhina in Borneo, where it can be found in forested areas within the island’s central highlands. Gray back, clean white underparts, and ginger-orange crest and face create a clean color palette.

name: Large-billed Antwren
rangeDescription: Brazilian plateau (piauí to mato grosso do sul) and northeastern bolivia
description: Small active antwren of the middle to upper levels of woodlands and dry forests. Males are gray with a black cap, a black white-tipped tail, and black wings with white bars.

name: Pesquet's Parrot
rangeDescription: Patchily distributed mountains of new guinea
description: A large, primitive parrot of lower-montane, foothill and nearby lowland primary forest. Unparrotlike, long, pointy head.

name: Lazuline Sabrewing
rangeDescription: Mountains of colombia, venezuela, and eastern ecuador
description: Large, distinctive hummingbird. Males have bright blue underparts with maroon tail and downcurved bill.
